<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - HIGH PRESSURE OIL PUMP -
        Installation - High Pressure OIl Pump Reservoir
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>High Pressure OIl Pump Reservoir</title>
        <figure id="f1201115" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3516.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Applying RTV Sealant to the Drive Gear Access Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">RTV Bead</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the access cover by applying RTV sealant to the front cover and the threads of the
                mounting bolts. Install the two mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Different types of reservoir gaskets are available. Make sure the correct type is being installed.
                    If the smaller gasket is used (not shown), apply RTV sealant to the rest of the mating surface.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1201116" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/eg6510.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing a Gasket on the Reservoir Mating Surface</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Reservoir Gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket on the top of the reservoir mating surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201117" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3376.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Back Pressure (EBP) Sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Reservoir Mounting Bolts (5)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the high pressure oil pump reservoir on the front cover. Secure the reservoir with
                five mounting bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201130" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3286.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the EBP Sensor</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Bracket Bolts (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube Nuts</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the two bolts that secure the EBP sensor bracket to the right side of the
                reservoir.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the EBP sensor tube to the right exhaust manifold. Tighten the tube nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the power steering pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill the reservoir with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the EBP sensor to the wiring harness.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201119" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3203.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR) Valve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Injection Pressure Regulator Valve (IPR)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, install the IPR valve. Tighten the valve to the special torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the solenoid and tinnermann nut. Tighten the tinnermann nut to the special torque
                value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the engine wiring harness connector to the solenoid.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201121" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3278.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the High Pressure Lube Oil Supply Hoses</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Lube Oil Supply Hoses (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the protective caps. Install both high pressure lube oil supply hoses at the high
                pressure pump fittings and cylinder head fittings. Tighten the fittings and secure the hoses to the
                special torque values.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
